
                   <p style="text-align: center">
                       <b>Title:</b> Suppose you plan to deploy three nodes on the same host: one Storage Node, one Admin Node, and one
Gateway Node. You should provide a minimum of nine storage volumes to the host. You will need a minimum
of 300 GB of performance-tier storage for the node containers, 670 GB of performance-tier storage for system
data and transaction logs, and 12 TB of capacity-tier storage for object data.<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=134, y1=523, x2=1566, y2=1423
